  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        The inclusion criteria of this study are:

          1. aged between 3 and 16 years

          2. diagnosed with congenital hemiplegic or children with CP with one more affected side;
             (3) apparently disuse phenomenon of the more affected hand at spontaneous contexts

        Participants will be exclude for:

          1. excessive muscle tone (Modified Ashworth Scale â‰¤ 2 at any joints of the upper limb)
             before beginning treatment (Bohannon &amp; Smith, 1987)

          2. severe cognitive, visual, or auditory disorders according to medical documents,
             parental reports, and the examiner's clinical observation

          3. injections of botulinum toxin type A or operations on the UE within 6 months
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
